TopicTitle: The whole solar system! [drawings] [You can participate]

Articles.Content:
Hi fellow forumer! Welcome to our little place, here we share art on solar system and beyond! 

-------------------

Introducing da squad:

@cubinator! the most awesome human being in the observable universe, that was friendly enough to help me with this project! He was and is my friend, he still carries on his legendary art.

Art style- pixel art

Bio- The artist who was first to join da club, his works are mostly asteroid, they are very enjoyable because of the very nice colors he uses.

-

 @AR3S_TGL! for also participating, he proved that you can be added to the OP without "mad skills" He is a nice dude, i liked that he was always courageous, no matter the stances.

Bio- He was intended to make a website, but instead he did some great art, and helped us Plutonian system, his art is very nice, not very representative, yet very bright in colors.

Art style- MS paint (similar to mine)

-

@ProtoJeb21!He is currently doing different exoplanet systems! He has his own folder! It is the last one! Worth to look at it! And i always enjoyed his renditions, he is very clever, i think, thank you.

Bio -Great artist who is a very clever exoplaneteer, knows a lot, does a lot, because he is just great man.

Art style- GIMP pictures

-

@Pine! An awesome artist you all love and know, is here to participate! Interesting thing is his unique style! Awesome! Thank you for your help! You are my inspiration.

Bio- although he did only one drawing, he did it so well, he made his way to the list of awesome people here, his art is known all over the forum. 

Art style- 3D modeling 

-

@mabdi36! Helped me with making gifts to the participants! He is soon going to make more new and awesome projects! You were a great guy! Keep on being like that.

Bio- He learned the style from on of my threads, mastered it and created a very nice banner for all of us, he is also doing little presents for advanced participants.

Art style - MSPaint miniatures

-

@Cabbink (Christ, that took 15 minutes to find him) He is also a GIMP artist! He does exoplanets! He is a solid participant, just like i wanted him to be, thank you.

Bio- also an exoplaneteer, he is very nice in doing art similar to what you can see in magazines and Wikipedia. You are a great dude.

Art style- GIMP pictures (doh!)

-

@Adstriduum! A sudden hero of this thread! His art is beyond detailed, it is lifelike! His art is great, thank you for everything! Carry on your legacy! You are great, you are the hero of your own story! Thank you !

Bio- artist who likes to show the whole system in just one picture, also does exoplanets, but does solar system objects too!

Art style- Paint.Net pixel art

-

@RoadRunnerAerospace! A pioneer of collaborating in this thread! One of the greatest part of his drawings-detail of the surface. He is an asteroid hunter! His art maybe were not seen for a while, but thank you anyway, thank you, thank you, thank you so much!

Bio- artist who likes to draw with mild, charming colors! His craters are drawn very realistic!

Art style-Pixel art

-

@ModerndayLink64! A new participator! He does both exoplanets (also exomoons) and solar system objects! He is very nice at drawing all sorts of objects, by that i mean, both gas giants and normal planets look equally great in his pictures! A great dude, although he didn't participate much, thank you, i love what you do, you have the future in your hands!

Bio-He recently joined the group at his free will, easily completed the first task and is now ready for next one!

Art style-GIMP pictures

-

@DeltaVerb! An artist with the most unique painting style! He is currently quite new to the forum, but that changes very quickly! Thank you for the things you done! You made my day once, you are also a hero of mine.

Bio-He is from Spain, joined by his own will, pretty talanted, although arts are quite simple, not very representative, but are just hyper-harmonic in their coloring.

Art style-flat design

-

@esinohio! He is a well known artist with an infinite potential! He also has his rare and unusual style! His art is the awesomeness itself! Thank you, i i love the things you draw, i love the way you draw, i love the way you use the talent you posses, thank you for disturbing the sound of silence for me.

Bio-Old and respected forumer, although he went silent for quite a long time, he is back in action with us!

Art style-Blender and photoshop pictures.

-

@DeltaDizzy! A great friend of mine! Also a very nice artist and mod developer! Now with us, showing what effort and love to the thing you do does! You are the greatness, made of bravery, talent and human flesh

Bio-After numerous attempts of drawing Rhea, ending up denied by me, i finally let him in. He is a very nice and friendly guy! His current only masterpiece is in the Saturn folder! It is really detailed and nice! Thank you dude, you are my friend, thank you for that.

----

@Kerbal101! Спасибо, большое человеческое спасибо от меня, вы помогли мне поверить в себя хоть и на короткое время, вы очень хороший модератор и это можно понять только посмотрев на всё что вы сделали для русского форума! Спасибо.

----

----

Now, it is me, writing my maybe last words here, i love you all, you are great.

Now, it is maybe the time for me to leave into the neon darkness, from where i came.

Thank you.
